---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
const lastUpdated = "March 2026";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Privacy Policy – Survive and Thrive"
  description="Privacy policy for the Survive and Thrive support group website."
>
  <section class="page-section container-pad policy-page">
    <div class="content-max">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="policy-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      Survive and Thrive is an independent, non-profit support group for people
      with ME, Fibromyalgia, and other Post-Viral Fatigue Syndromes, based in
      the High Peak. Our website address is
      <strong>surviveandthrivesupportgroup.com</strong>.
    </p>
    <p>
      We are not a registered company or charity. We are a volunteer-run
      community group. Any questions about this policy or your personal data can
      be sent to us via the <a href="/contact-us">Contact Us</a> page.
    </p>

    <h2>What information we collect</h2>
    <p>
      We only collect information you provide to us voluntarily through our
      contact form or chat widget:
    </p>
    <ul class="policy-list">
      <li>Your name (optional)</li>
      <li>Your email address (required — so we can reply)</li>
      <li>Your phone number (optional)</li>
      <li>The content of your message</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We do not collect any other personal information automatically. We do not
      use analytics services, tracking pixels, or advertising networks.
    </p>

    <h2>How we use your information</h2>
    <p>
      Information submitted through our contact forms is used solely to respond
      to your enquiry. We do not share it with any third parties, add you to
      mailing lists, or use it for any marketing purpose.
    </p>

    <h2>Legal basis for processing (UK GDPR)</h2>
    <p>
      We process your contact details on the basis of <strong>legitimate
      interests</strong> (Article 6(1)(f) UK GDPR) — specifically, to be able
      to respond to enquiries sent to us directly by you.
    </p>

    <h2>How long we keep your data</h2>
    <p>
      Enquiry emails are retained only for as long as needed to handle your
      query, after which they are deleted. We do not maintain a separate
      database of enquiry data.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      Our website does not use tracking or analytics cookies. We use
      <strong>Cloudflare Turnstile</strong> on our contact forms to prevent
      spam. Turnstile may set a small number of strictly necessary cookies
      required for security verification. No personal data is stored in these
      cookies and they are not used for advertising.
    </p>
    <p>
      Further details on Cloudflare's data practices can be found in the
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/en-gb/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party services</h2>
    <p>
      Our website is hosted on <strong>Cloudflare</strong>. Cloudflare may
      process request metadata (such as IP addresses) as part of providing
      hosting and security services.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our website embeds a <strong>Google Maps</strong> map on the Meetings
      page. Google may set cookies when you interact with the map. Please refer
      to the <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Privacy Policy</a> for details.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our website displays <strong>Instagram</strong> embedded posts on the
      home page. Instagram/Meta may set cookies when you interact with those
      embeds. Please refer to the
      <a href="https://privacycenter.instagram.com/policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Instagram Privacy Policy</a> for details.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights under UK GDPR</h2>
    <p>You have the right to:</p>
    <ul class="policy-list">
      <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
      <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
      <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
      <li>Object to our processing of your data</li>
      <li>Lodge a complaint with the ICO (Information Commissioner's Office)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      To exercise any of these rights, please contact us via the
      <a href="/contact-us">Contact Us</a> page. You can also contact the ICO
      at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a>
      or by calling 0303 123 1113.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy from time to time. The date at the top of this
      page shows when it was last revised.
    </p>
</div><!-- /.content-max -->
  </section>
</MainLayout>
